CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. It is used to style and design HTML elements on a web page—like colors, fonts, layouts, and spacing.

History of CSS :===
 1.  CSS 1 (1996) :-
     Introduced by W3C.
     Basic styling: fonts, colors, text alignment.
2. CSS 2 (1998) :-
   Added positioning, z-index, media types
   Improved control over page layout.
3. CSS 2.1 (2011) :-
   Updated CSS 2 with bug fixes and browser compatibility.
4. CSS3 (2011 onwards)
   Modular approach (easier updates).
    Advanced features:-
   Animations & transitions.
   Flexbox & Grid for layouts.
